abstract_ssm: George Breitman (1916-1986) was a Trotskyist and a founding member of the Socialist Workers Party (SWP). He edited The Militant newspaper and served in World War II. In the 1960s, Breitman assumed responsibility for the SWP's Pathfinder Press, edited Writings of Leon Trotsky, 1929-1940, and wrote Malcolm X Speaks (1965). The George Breitman Papers contain personal files, correspondence, files of the Socialist Workers Party and other socialist organizations, written works, audio recordings of events and lectures, and photographs. The materials portay Breitman's life and work, including scholarly work and activism relating to U.S. socialism, Trotskyism, Malcolm X, and the Black Power and Civil Rights movements.
